  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../library/release-china-releases-first-guidelines-carbon-capture-use-and-storage">RELEASE: China releases the first guidelines on carbon capture, use and storage</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"><div class="filefield-file"><img class="filefield-icon field-icon-application-pdf"  alt="application/pdf icon" src="../sites/all/modules/filefield/icons/application-pdf.png" /><a href="../files/chinainfo/Release_CCS_Guidelines.pdf" type="application/pdf; length=300074">Release_CCS_Guidelines.pdf</a></div></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>The Guidelines for Carbon Dioxide Capture, Utilization, and Storage (CCUS) in China, prepared under a cooperative project of the Tsinghua BP Center and the World Resources Institute, is released in Beijing today.</p>

<p>The Guidelines are the first detailed examination of CCUS regulations in China. It provides a complete set of recommendations for how to regulate CCUS in its technical, environmental and social dimensions.</p></div>
  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-20 views-row-even">
      
  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../blog-posts/chinas-climate-minister-supports-carbon-capture-and-storage">China‚Äôs Climate Minister Speaks in Support of Carbon Capture and Storage, Two New Potential Projects Announced</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/ccs_7-28-11.jpg" alt="" title="" width="162" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-library-file-fid">
                <div class="field-content"></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>China‚Äôs Climate Change Minister Xie Zhenhua offered a new phrase to emphasize the importance of technologies to reduce carbon in a speech at a <a href="http://beta.adb.org/news/events/international-carbon-capture-and-storage-ccs-conference">major international conference</a> on <a href="http://www.wri.org/project/carbon-dioxide-capture-storage">Carbon Capture and Storage</a> (CCS) in Beijing, July 27.  Minister Xie said that China‚Äôs energy and environment policies support ‚Äúenergy efficiency and carbon reduction‚Äù (jieneng jiantan).</p></div>
