<p>Energy and water constraints have emerged as critical sustainability issues for China‚Äôs economy ‚Äì particularly if the country is to continue to see significant GDP growth and provide the estimated 10 million jobs needed annually. Asia Water Project recently posed questions about the water-energy nexus to Professor Zou Ji, WRI&#8217;s China Country Director, and Lijin Zhong and Hua Wen of WRI&#8217;s China Water Team. Their responses are below:</p></div>
  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-23 views-row-odd">
      
